# Tokens

Design tokens for headings use a modular scale system with base values and ratios to automatically calculate font sizes, weights, and spacing across all heading levels.

| Token                               | Description                                        | Default Value                |
| ----------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| `--heading-font-family`             | Font family for all heading levels                 | `var(--font-family-heading)` |
| `--heading-font-size`               | Font size for `<h1>` (largest heading)             | `2.5rem`                     |
| `--heading-font-size-ratio`         | Multiplier for scaling font sizes between levels   | `0.8`                        |
| `--heading-font-weight`             | Font weight for `<h1>`                             | `700`                        |
| `--heading-font-weight-decrement`   | Amount to reduce font weight per level             | `50`                         |
| `--heading-line-height`             | Line height for all headings                       | `1.2`                        |
| `--heading-letter-spacing`          | Letter spacing for all headings                    | `-0.02em`                    |
| `--heading-margin-top`              | Top margin for `<h1>`                              | `var(--space-12)`            |
| `--heading-margin-bottom`           | Bottom margin for `<h1>`                           | `var(--space-4)`             |
| `--heading-margin-ratio`            | Ratio for scaling margins between levels           | `0.8`                        |
| `--heading-color`                   | Text color for all headings                        | `var(--text-color-primary)`  |
| `--heading-color-opacity-decrement` | Amount to reduce opacity per level (0 = no change) | `0`                          |

# Usage

The heading system uses three key token types to automatically calculate all heading properties:

**Base tokens** define the starting point for `<h1>`:

- `--heading-font-size: 2.5rem` - h1 font size
- `--heading-font-weight: 700` - h1 font weight
- `--heading-margin-top: var(--space-12)` - h1 top margin

**Ratio tokens** control multiplicative scaling from the base. For example, if `--heading-font-size: 2.5rem` and `--heading-font-size-ratio: 0.8` then,

- h1 = `2.5rem`
- h2 = `2rem` (2.5 × 0.8)
- h3 = `1.6rem` (2 × 0.8)

**Decrement tokens** control linear reduction from the base. For example, if `--heading-font-weight: 700` and `--heading-font-weight-decrement: 50` then,

- h1 = `700`
- h2 = `650` (700 - 50)
- h3 = `600` (650 - 50)

For quick customization, focus on these tokens:

- `--heading-color` - Change all heading colors at once
- `--heading-font-size` - Sets overall heading scale
- `--heading-font-size-ratio` - Controls hierarchy contrast (0.9 = subtle, 0.7 = dramatic)
- `--heading-font-weight` - Make headings lighter or bolder
- `--heading-font-weight-decrement` - Fine-tune weight progression
- `--heading-margin-top` - Adjust spacing above headings
- `--heading-margin-ratio` - Control margin scaling independently from font sizes

# Patterns

## Compact Headings

Ideal for documentation, technical content, or high-density information:

```css
:root {
  --heading-font-size: 1.875rem;
  --heading-font-size-ratio: 0.833; /* Minor Third inverted - subtle differences */
  --heading-margin-top: var(--space-6);
  --heading-margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  --heading-font-weight: 600;
  --heading-color: var(--color-blue-900);
}
```

```html raw
<div
  style="
  --heading-font-size: 1.875rem;
  --heading-font-size-ratio: 0.833;
  --heading-margin-top: var(--space-6);
  --heading-margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  --heading-font-weight: 600;
  --heading-color: var(--color-blue-900);
"
>
  <h1>Heading One</h1>
  <h2>Heading Two</h2>
  <h3>Heading Three</h3>
  <h4>Heading Four</h4>
  <h5>Heading Five</h5>
  <h6>Heading Six</h6>
</div>
```

